var title_f0_20_324="G protein structure";
var content_f0_20_324=[" <div id=\"graphicsToolbar\">",
"  <div id=\"graphicsCopy\">",
"   &copy;2013 UpToDate",
"   <sup>",
"    &reg;",
"   </sup>",
"  </div>",
"  <div id=\"graphicsLinks\">",
"   <a href=\"?imageKey=GAST%2F63760&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\">",
"    <img alt=\"Print this page\" src=\"./../images/icn_print.myextg\" title=\"Print this page\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink\" href=\"?imageKey=GAST%2F63760&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\" title=\"Print this page\">",
"    Print",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"etacLink\" href=\"#\">",
"    <img alt=\"Email graphic(s)\" src=\"./../images/icn_email.myextg\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink etacLink\" href=\"#\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\">",
"    Email",
"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 480px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Structure of a G protein coupled receptor",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 460px; height: 340px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The molecular structure of a G protein coupled receptor includes seven membrane spanning domains, a carboxy end (COOH) and an amino end (NH3). The amino end, which is glycosylated (in green) resides on the outside of the cell and for most peptide hormones participates in binding. The carboxy end is located inside the cell and contains many sites of phosphorylation (in red). These regions are phosphorylated by regulatory proteins and often assist in receptor desensitization.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Courtesy of Michael A Shetzline, MD, PhD and Rodger A Liddle, MD.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
"</div>"].join("\n");
